      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's a good start, quite atmospheric. Now I want to ground it a bit more. I need to describe the actual people walking through this area to really set the tone for the protagonist. \n\nCan you add some details about the types of people hanging out on the corners or walking the sidewalks? I want to capture that sense of \"danger\" you mentioned—describe the specific groups or types of characters that would make a stranger feel like they're in the wrong part of town. Make it feel real and unpolished.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
